Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Afribank of Nigeria, Intercontinental

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-07-06T15:47:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-afribank-of-nigeria-intercontinental.html
The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share
Index fell for a fourth day, retreating 0.9 percent to 24,256.97
by the 2:30 p.m. close of trading in Lagos, according to an e-
mailed statement from the bourse.  Namibia ’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  retreated for the
first day in nine, losing 0.9 percent to 856.17 at the 4 p.m.
close in Windhoek. Kenya’s All-Share Index declined for a second
day, falling 0.2 percent to 69.90 by the 3 p.m. close in
Nairobi, the lowest since June 24. Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index
snapped two days of gains, declining 0.3 to 2,098.44 by the 1:30
p.m. close in  Port Louis . The Ghana Stock Exchange Composite
Index rose for the first day in three, increasing 0.02 percent
to 1,187.13 by the 3 p.m. close in Accra.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Oceanic Bank International Plc (OCEANIC)  , a Nigerian
lender bailed out by the central bank in 2009, slid 7 kobo, or
4.9 percent, to 1.37 naira, its biggest drop since June 13,
after the central bank threatened to nationalize lenders if they
failed to meet a Sept. 30 recapitalization deadline.  Intercontinental Bank Plc (INTERCON)   declined for a
third day, dropping 1 kobo, or 1 percent, to 97 kobo. Afribank
Plc (AFRIBANK NL) retreated 5 kobo, or 4.2 percent, to 1.13
naira, the lowest closing price since June 20.  Finbank Plc (FIRSTINL) 
 fell 1 kobo, or 1.8 percent, to 55 kobo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
